  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Application processes vary by program. Federal MM2H goes through the Ministry of Tourism; S-MM2H through Sarawak state. Both require substantial documentation.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">MM2H (Federal) Application Process</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Document Preparation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Gather: passport copies, financial statements showing RM1.5M liquid assets, bank statements showing RM40K/month income, police clearance certificate, CV/resume, cover letter.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply through authorized MM2H agent or directly to Tourism Malaysia. Most applicants use agents for smoother process. Agent fees RM3,000-10,000. Submit online and physical documents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Ministry Review</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Tourism Malaysia processes application (3-6 months). May request additional documents. Background checks conducted. Quota system means some waiting.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Conditional Approval</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Upon approval, receive conditional approval letter. You have 6 months to fulfill requirements: open Malaysian bank account, deposit RM1M, obtain medical insurance, complete medical checkup.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Endorsement</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">After fulfilling conditions, receive MM2H visa endorsement in passport. Valid 5 years, renewable. Register with Immigration upon each entry. 90-day reporting not required (unlike Thailand).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">S-MM2H (Sarawak) Application Process</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Document Preparation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Similar documents to federal MM2H but lower financial thresholds. Passport, financial statements (RM150K-300K liquid), income proof (RM10K/month), police clearance, medical checkup.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit to Sarawak Tourism</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply through Sarawak Tourism Board or authorized agent. Processing typically faster than federal (2-4 months). Fewer applications mean shorter queues.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Approval & Banking</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Upon approval, open Sarawak bank account and deposit required amount. Obtain insurance if 50+. Complete medical checkup at Sarawak hospital.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Issuance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Receive S-MM2H visa (5 or 10-year option). Can live in Sarawak and travel freely throughout Malaysia. Renewable upon expiry. Commitment to reside primarily in Sarawak.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Agent recommendation:</strong> Most successful applicants use authorized agents. They know current requirements, common issues, and can navigate bureaucracy. Cost RM3,000-10,000 but usually worth it for smoother process, especially for federal MM2H. For S-MM2H, direct application is more feasible.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

