  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Post-2021 Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Federal MM2H requirements increased dramatically in 2021. RM1M deposit and RM40K/month income are non-negotiable. If you can't meet these, consider S-MM2H (RM150K-300K) or other SE Asia options. Don't waste time applying without qualifying funds.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Unclear Income Documentation</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Ministry requires clear, verifiable offshore income. Cryptocurrency, day trading, or vague "investments" typically rejected. Document pension, employment, rental income, or business profits with clear paper trail. Bank statements should show consistent deposits.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Letting Insurance Lapse</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Insurance is a visa condition for MM2H participants aged 35+. If coverage lapses, you're technically in violation. Renew before expiry. Set calendar reminders. Some applicants have had renewal issues—maintain continuous coverage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Work Rights</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">MM2H allows limited part-time work (with endorsement) but not regular employment. You cannot compete with Malaysians for jobs. If you need to work, consider Labuan setup, Employment Pass, or another country. Remote work for overseas employers is generally tolerated.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Property Price Minimums</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Foreigners can buy property but minimums apply—typically RM1M+ (varies by state). You cannot buy the RM300K condo you found online. Research state-specific rules. Strata titles (condos) easier than landed property. Lawyer essential for property purchase.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

